Full Job Description Langan provides expert land development engineering and environmental consulting services for major developers, corporations, energy companies, healthcare systems, colleges/universities, and large infrastructure programs throughout the U.S. and around the world. Our employees collaborate seamlessly among 30+ offices and gain valuable hands-on experience that fosters career growth. Langan culture is entrepreneurial from advancing innovative technical solutions, to participating in robust training and knowledge sharing, to making progressive change within the communities we live and work.

Langan is committed to a diverse and inclusive work environment where employees are empowered to contribute their skills and knowledge to make impactful contributions. Langan is pleased to be recognized for three consecutive years as a top 10 "Best Firms to Work For" and top 100 "Hot Firms" in the nation.

Langan is seeking a winter (December 2021 - January 2022) IT Help Desk Cooperative Education Student or Intern to join its Help Desk team at its headquarters in Parsippany, NJ. This individual will serve a key function in troubleshooting technical issues and repairing and maintaining all types of computer and peripheral hardware. In this role, you will have the opportunity to work on exciting projects and will work in a team environment while gaining practical experience.

Job Responsibilities:
Set up and repair PCs and peripherals;
Perform software installations;
Minor printer repair and support;
Occasionally provide telephone, e-mail, and live chat technical support; and
Perform other duties as requested.

Qualifications:
Student actively pursuing a four year or advanced degree in Information Technology, Computer Science or related field;
Minimum GPA of 3.0;
Excellent communication skills, written and verbal;
Strong attention to detail with excellent customer service skills;
Ability to effectively work independently and in a team environment;
Proficiency with MS Office applications;
Ability to travel to satellite offices to provide on-site support;
Programming and/or networking experience a plus; and
Data entry, inventory and video editing experience preferred.

Please submit your resume, cover letter and academic transcripts.

Langan does not provide housing or relocation assistance for internship/co-op positions.

Langan is committed to employee wellbeing and providing a healthy and safe work environment. Langan provides a rich array of programs and benefits to help its employees advance their careers and enhance the quality of their lives. Our comprehensive compensation package includes: full-time employment company paid medical, dental, and vision coverage; life insurance, short- and long-term disability insurance, and paid pregnancy disability leave; 401(k)/Roth with company match; paid time off including parental and military leave; employee referral and professional license bonuses; and educational reimbursement.

Langan offers flexible work schedules; extensive training; wellness programs; buddy and mentoring programs; employee resource groups; and much more!

Langan is an affirmative action / equal opportunity employer committed to building a team that represents and values diverse backgrounds. Langan promotes a positive work environment of inclusion, where we respect each other’s differences and recognize that a diverse and inclusive environment is a key to our success.

Full Job Description Description

Encompass Technologies is a Fort Collins, CO based company that provides an ERP solution to the food and beverage distribution industry (think Red Bull, Schwann's, and Beer and you’ll start to get it). We provide a web-based, mobile device-deployed solution that improves our clients’ accounting, inventory, delivery, warehousing, route planning, and productivity. That means we enable the delivery of food, beer, and other beverages across the nation. And in some cases, the world.

An internship with us is where the fun begins. Our hands-on interns learn how to make decisions about design and feature implementation using technical tools. They write code, design efficient data structures and algorithms for web-based applications, turn concepts into new features, and basically bring our products to life. Our interns interact with the service and support team as well as with customers. (This is not like Technical Support; it requires applying a cross-functional business/accounting and technical skill set to a variety of customer inquiries.)

Compensation for this paid internship is $20/hour. Hours are flexible but interns are required to be available, on-site at the office, for at least 20 hours/week but less than of 30 hours/week.

We have the coolest office in Fort Collins, right on the banks of the Poudre in Old Town. If you enjoy working hard, having fun, proving yourself, being a hero to your customers, and grabbing a beer (well... if you're at least 21), you will enjoy this environment.

Please note - Encompass will not sponsor applicants for work visas. At this time, we are only able to consider people who have the following status: Lawful Permanent Residents, Asylees, Refugees, and U.S. Citizens.

Requirements

We Hire Interns Who:
Are pursuing a Bachelors Degree in Computer Science or a related field and related software experience;
Are organized, resourceful, independent and strong communicators;
Learn quickly and thrive in an environment of multi –tasking;
Demonstrate a “can-do” attitude, and are highly motivated;
Possess strong critical thinking, problem solving, and customer service and interaction skills;
Have excellent written and verbal communication skills;
Are able to take initiative and work independently;
Have a strong knowledge of Windows operating systems, browsers and the internet;
Have knowledge of computer hardware and software, demonstrated skills in software design and development, and proven skills in troubleshooting and solving complex software problems.

This Won’t Be the Right Environment For Those Who:
Need detailed training and hand-holding;
Want to be left alone and uninvolved;
Lack confidence and self-awareness;
Don’t want to work hard;
Are cocky
